Admin:
1. Login Page
Both users and administrators are pre-registered in the hostel allocation system. Users must enter
the proper correct username and password in order to log in to the system.
2. Dashboard
The total number of students in each year, regardless of their courses, is represented
graphically with male and female students being distinguished. Additionally, the dashboard
displays the total number of students, blocks, and rooms in each college.
Details of recent actions taken against students are shown in the section titled Recent Activity
including date, time and the destined room.
3. Block Page
The block's name, overall room count and total student are all listed in each block. SSOs may even
modify and remove the Block from the dashboard in accordance to the condition.Additionally, it
displays the block's current status.
● Add block
The "Add block" button allows SSOs to add new blocks, which they must then specify the block name,
type (male or female), and status (available or unavailable).
● Edit and delete block
By selecting the update and delete actions, the admin can change the block name, hostel type, and
status if necessary.
● View room
The information about each student's roommates is accessible to SSO.
● Creating rooms from the block page
Adding a room can also be done from the block page, having to provide the room name, room
capacity, room status, and whether or not the room is accessible for people with disabilities.
● Deleting students from particular room (exceptional cases)
SSO has the authority to remove the student if necessary (exceptional cases such as suspension) upon
clicking the delete action.
4. Add Room page
SSO can manually add a room to the hostel by choosing an existing block, assigning a room name,
determining the room's capacity, and specifying whether or not the room is accessible for people with
disabilities and the room's status if it's available, it's marked as active, otherwise, it's not.
5. Allocation Page
The system allows SSOs to select a year which will display the allocation details of the searched year.
SSO can also download the allocation data or print it. To create the current Academic year, click the
‘create academic year’ button and specify the proposed session(i.e July2024-June2025).
Then SSO must select the particular group of students based on their courses to allocate. Then SSO
must select the block for each gender depending on number of students and the slots, then the system
automatically allocates rooms to students clicking the ALLOCATE button.
6. Search Page
This is the page with the student and room details.
● Search by Room name
The search button visible in the picture displays the details of the particular room details, i.e it
will display the previous allocated student when searched by room name.
● Search by Student name
When a student is searched by name, a list of the rooms they have stayed over the past year will
also be displayed.
● Search by Block name.
When a Block is searched by name, the particular Block will be displayed where the details of
the room can be accessible for SSO if needed.
● Search for Student details
The SSO can search for "student details" based on the student's room, which will display
information about the student's current room name, room capacity, room status, hostel type, and
the current room occupants.
● Search for Room details
The SSO can search for "room details" based on the student's ID, which will display information
about the student name, student's ID, gender, RUB email id, courses, and the year.
7. Request Page
The requested hostel change applied by the students will be displayed on the request page including
their profile pic, their current designated room and the destined room, and even the details of the
time and date they have requested.
When clicked on any of the names listed in the request page, the page directed will be the details
of the student, which includes name, courses with year, their current room and block, destined
room the block. In addition the student must provide the reason and must attach a file for the room
change. Depending on the reason SSO can either accept nor reject the request.
● Rejection and acception statement
If there are two or more requests for a particular room to be changed, the admin will accept the
request for the most genuine justification and file attached by the Students. When an admin accepts
or rejects a request, the admin provides a statement outlining their reasoning.
● History for the room change request
For the duration of one academic session, on clicking the “History” button all the room change
request history will be accumulated in this page. SSO can see their history of ACCEPTED and
REJECTED history with the reason against the name and the courses of the student.
8. Handicapped page
The SSOs allocate the rooms manually for those students with special needs. There will be
pre-reserved rooms for those students in advance. SSOs must possess a list of those students.
SSO must allocate room based on their SID.
Student:
1. Login Page
Both users and administrators are pre-registered in the hostel allocation system. Users must enter
the proper correct username and password in order to log in to the system.
2. Landing Page for User
The user will be greeted with the welcome message as soon as they log in to their account.
3. Profile Details
The user's image will also be displayed along with his or her own information and other
information.
4. Roommates Details
The system allows students to view the details of their assigned rooms, including roommates,
block name and the roomname.
5. Room Change Request
The system includes a feature that allows students to request a room change to an available
empty room. A student must provide justification and upload a relevant file if he wants to
switch rooms. When a student requests a hostel change, the system should notify the Student
Services Officer, which is in charge of managing hostel accommodations. If the rooms are
available and SSO accepts the request as genuine, the student will receive an approval email
and if SSO rejects the request, the student will receive a rejection email with the rejection
statement.
6. Room change request
On the user side the status of the room change request will be displayed depending upon the
action done by the SSO along with the acceptance and rejection statement.
● Remarks
7. Dark mode
For the user side, we apply dark mode features to enhance the ability to see and perceive objects
in environments with limited or insufficient lighting conditions. And also to reduce eye strain,
enhance readability, save energy, improve focus, and accommodate users with visual impairments
or light sensitivity.
8. Logout
Students can logout from the system
